# Code standards (FlowOS)

Full doc: [docs/foundation/governance/CODE_STANDARDS.md](docs/foundation/governance/CODE_STANDARDS.md)

## Default behavior

- **Smallest diff** — no drive-by refactors, palette sweeps, or file splits in M2.
- **Match the touched area** — copy patterns from sibling files before inventing new ones.
- **Compose, don't fork** — reuse existing page shells, dialogs, strips.

## Where code goes

| Path | Use |
|------|-----|
| `src/app/(main)/` | Authenticated routes |
| `src/components/ui/` | Shared primitives |
| `src/components/{feature}/` | Feature UI |
| `src/lib/` | Pure logic, palettes, Supabase helpers |
| `src/hooks/`, `src/contexts/`, `src/config/`, `src/types/` | As named |

New `lib/` domains → update `FEATURE_INVENTORY.md`. Files: `kebab-case`; components: `PascalCase`; imports: `@/…`.

## React

- Server Components by default; `"use client"` only when hooks/events/DOM needed — keep boundary low.
- Logic in `lib/`, not duplicated in JSX. Extend `schedule-palette.ts`, `*-appearance.ts` for colors — not inline hex.
- No fake/placeholder shipped controls.

## Styling

- Semantic tokens from `src/app/globals.css` (`bg-card`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`, …).
- Dark only. Critical controls **visible without hover** (PRINCIPLES #10).

## Data, routes, security (never defer)

- User-scoped Supabase queries; RLS on new tables; no `using (true)` on user data.
- New auth route → `PROTECTED_PREFIXES` in `src/middleware.ts` + sidebar/FEATURE_INVENTORY if visible.
- Schema → `supabase/*.sql` + `src/types/database.ts`.

## Before merge (on branch)

`npm run build` && `npm run lint` — no new errors in touched files. Manual smoke on changed flow. Founder approval for `main` (see `git-workflow.mdc`).

## M2 out of scope

Command palette, new modules, dnd-kit migration, monolith refactors, visual polish unless runbook session says so.
